Method Detail

update

public void update()
            throws IOException
Description copied from interface: ResourceLoader
Update the resource output by parsing the ResourceLocations. The locations are accessed via the ResourceLoader.getLocation(String) method. If an attempt is made to retrieve a location that does not existing then a MissingLocationException is thrown. The ResourceLoader.canUpdate() method can be called to ensure all required locations are available and the loader should be able to 'update'. This method is allowed to throw an IOException but should be reserved for major failures. There may well be cases where an IOException will be thrown on a single record of thousands. This should be logged and not thrown (note: logging access has not currently been implemented).

Throws:
IOException - could not load resources
